<subSubSection id="452203CF94B9002F501AFAA7E4F37A6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph id="B65E779EC0E19931460C30742A4AF71B" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09AA5C65651A40DFED8059726FECB2D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Frustule is cylindrical, valve flat, 15.7-46.6 
<normalizedToken id="E3E0529B5D018E6636ADD069B5C10613" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter with numerous small-scale granules, 5.7-15.5 
<normalizedToken id="CBFAFD54F6D366491ED251263E045398" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
high (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E9137E9AB6D5C973CAF9BF376B20385E" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. SEM (A-D, H) and LM (E-G) images of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city: A-G Melosira subglobosa (A, F girdle views, B-E, G, valve views) H Melosira varians, partial valve view and girdle view of complete frustule. Scale bars: 10 μm (A-C, E-H); 20 μm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545734" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D7B8DF97482699469FE1A724FF510BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="860EE4657E0E98D0815FD8D8BA9D2317" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B685F820F9B8726C22AB6E4BB7A9E1A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Common species for freshwaters in streams and lakes, as well as in slightly brackish waters, oligotrophic, eutrophic to dystrophic or polluted environments (
<bibRefCitation id="817F326C31568E1DBC26A1EE86444459" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/1676-0611-bn-2016-0249" author="Nardelli, MS" journalOrPublisher="Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B96" refString="Nardelli, MS, Tremarin, PI, Ludwig, TA, Bueno, NC, 2016. Melosira (Diatomeae) taxa from the Iguacu River in southern Brazil. Biota Neotropica 16(4): e20160249. https://doi.org/10.1590/1676-0611-bn-2016-0249" title="Melosira (Diatomeae) taxa from the Iguacu River in southern Brazil. Biota Neotropica 16 (4): e 20160249." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/1676-0611-bn-2016-0249" year="2016">Nardelli et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="BA652CF80450C9A97EF1652D23F99068" author="Hofmann, G" editor="Metzing, D" journalOrPublisher="Band 7: Pflanzen. Landwirtschaftsverlag, Muenster, Naturschutz und Biologische Vielfalt 70 (7)" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="601 - 708" refId="B57" refString="Hofmann, G, Lange-Bertalot, H, Werum, M, Klee, R unter Mitarbeit von Koenig C, Kusber, W-H, Metzeltin, D, Reichardt, E, 2018. Rote Liste und Gesamtartenliste der limnischen Kieselalgen (Bacillariophyta) Deutschlands. In: Metzing, D, Hofbauer, NL, Hajek, GM, Eds., Rote Liste gefaehrdeter Tiere, Pflanzen und Pilze Deutschlands. Band 7: Pflanzen. Landwirtschaftsverlag, Muenster, Naturschutz und Biologische Vielfalt 70(7): 601 - 708" title="Rote Liste und Gesamtartenliste der limnischen Kieselalgen (Bacillariophyta) Deutschlands." volumeTitle="Rote Liste gefaehrdeter Tiere, Pflanzen und Pilze Deutschlands." year="2018">Hofmann et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Taxon has preferences of alkaline conditions (pH 7-8.5), with moderate oxygen, regularly found in humid environments, requiring periodically high levels of nitrogen (
<bibRefCitation id="28A789A942F1318F8D3BC7E46D9D93C3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-010-0006-5" author="Soltanpour-Gargari, A" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Croatica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="167 - 190" refId="B115" refString="Soltanpour-Gargari, A, Lodenius, M, Hinz, F, 2011. Epilithic diatoms (Bacillariophyceae) from streams in Ramsar, Iran. Acta Botanica Croatica 70 (2): 167 - 190, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-010-0006-5" title="Epilithic diatoms (Bacillariophyceae) from streams in Ramsar, Iran." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-010-0006-5" volume="70" year="2011">Soltanpour-Gargari et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1C4DB1A287D412252EA20A2CA56A4A68" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D226C9A12C893DD32B2EA17E7A5CDADF" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C08130CC6B8C0525771442C4163766A" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Valves were found near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in our previous sampling study (Table 
<tableCitation id="8FF8C24333628A204EC6B36AED07F0B8" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="97270C1A96071A9552CB095D7474D21B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1615/InterJAlgae.v17.i4.20" author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="International Journal on Algae" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="339 - 350" refId="B40" refString="Genkal, SI, Bilous, OP, 2015. Centric Diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Lower Portion of the Southern Bug River (Ukraine). International Journal on Algae 17 (4): 339 - 350, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1615/InterJAlgae.v17.i4.20" title="Centric Diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Lower Portion of the Southern Bug River (Ukraine)." url="https://doi.org/10.1615/InterJAlgae.v17.i4.20" volume="17" year="2015">Genkal and Bilous 2015</bibRefCitation>
). In Ukraine, it is known from the Southern Bug and lakes in the basins of the rivers Danube, Dnister, Siverskyi Donets, Desna, Prypiat, Dnipro and its reservoirs and estuary.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9415CD90D9CAD2324969C5EEC7273E9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
On the global level, it is a widely distributed taxon, known from Europe (i.e. Berlin, Germany, see 
<bibRefCitation id="DD54BA1A32DC622BDD20B2571EA64B54" author="Geissler, U" journalOrPublisher="Beiheft" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 777" refId="B35" refString="Geissler, U, Kies, L, 2003. Artendiversitaet und Veraenderungen in der Algenflora zweier staedtischer Ballungsgebiete Deutschlands: Berlin und Hamburg (Diversity and dynamics of the freshwater algal flora in two urban areas of Germany: Berlin and Hamburg). Nova Hedwigia. Beiheft 126: 1 - 777" title="Artendiversitaet und Veraenderungen in der Algenflora zweier staedtischer Ballungsgebiete Deutschlands: Berlin und Hamburg (Diversity and dynamics of the freshwater algal flora in two urban areas of Germany: Berlin and Hamburg). Nova Hedwigia." volume="126" year="2003">Geissler and Kies 2003</bibRefCitation>
), Russia (
<bibRefCitation id="38B16E21D6D2C143D571F8A67BF84312" author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B45" refString="Genkal, SI, Kulikovskiy, MS, Kuznetsova, IV, 2020. Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]." year="2020">Genkal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
), Asia (Iran), North America (Canada, USA), Africa (Egypt, RSA); Adriatic, Aral, Azov, Baltic, Barents, Black, Caspian, Kara, Mediterranean, North and Red Seas, and throughout North America (
<bibRefCitation id="B8C31C8DA29D2973D78079B762D1EA0B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-012741550-5/50016-7" author="Stoermer, EF" editor="Wehr, JD" journalOrPublisher="San Diego, Academic Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="559 - 594" refId="B118" refString="Stoermer, EF, Julius, ML, 2003. Centric diatoms. In: Wehr, JD, Sheath, RG, Eds., Freshwater algae of North America: ecology and classification. San Diego, Academic Press: 559 - 594, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-012741550-5/50016-7" title="Centric diatoms." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-012741550-5/50016-7" volumeTitle="Freshwater algae of North America: ecology and classification." year="2003">Stoermer and Julius 2003</bibRefCitation>
). It is also very common in Brazilian waters (
<bibRefCitation id="DD22CF75AD4FE4F5E1648151709F081A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-012741550-5/50016-7" author="Stoermer, EF" editor="Wehr, JD" journalOrPublisher="San Diego, Academic Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="559 - 594" refId="B118" refString="Stoermer, EF, Julius, ML, 2003. Centric diatoms. In: Wehr, JD, Sheath, RG, Eds., Freshwater algae of North America: ecology and classification. San Diego, Academic Press: 559 - 594, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-012741550-5/50016-7" title="Centric diatoms." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/B978-012741550-5/50016-7" volumeTitle="Freshwater algae of North America: ecology and classification." year="2003">Stoermer and Julius 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CBCB5D4AD6F71CB3FCAA756641F16002" author="Tremarin, PI" journalOrPublisher="Serie Botanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="79 - 107" publicationUrl="https://isb.emnuvens.com.br/iheringia/article/view/123/130" refId="B125" refString="Tremarin, PI, Freire, EG, Bertolli, LM, Ludwig, TAV, 2009. Catalogo das diatomaceas (Ochrophyta -Diatomeae) continentais do estado do Parana. Iheringia. Serie Botanica 64: 79 - 107, https://isb.emnuvens.com.br/iheringia/article/view/123/130" title="Catalogo das diatomaceas (Ochrophyta - Diatomeae) continentais do estado do Parana. Iheringia." url="https://isb.emnuvens.com.br/iheringia/article/view/123/130" volume="64" year="2009">Tremarin et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="086B45213B176D2CD70F02BC34E2C17B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/1676-0611-bn-2016-0249" author="Nardelli, MS" journalOrPublisher="Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B96" refString="Nardelli, MS, Tremarin, PI, Ludwig, TA, Bueno, NC, 2016. Melosira (Diatomeae) taxa from the Iguacu River in southern Brazil. Biota Neotropica 16(4): e20160249. https://doi.org/10.1590/1676-0611-bn-2016-0249" title="Melosira (Diatomeae) taxa from the Iguacu River in southern Brazil. Biota Neotropica 16 (4): e 20160249." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/1676-0611-bn-2016-0249" year="2016">Nardelli et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
